The paper discusses a variant of the variational autoencoder model for unsupervised clustering, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on deep generative models and their application to clustering, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses visualizations to provide intuition about the clustering process, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of heuristics to improve clustering performance, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
